  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "389 Directory Server is an LDAP version 3 (LDAPv3) compliant server. The base packages include the Lightweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) server and command-line utilities for server administration.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* 389-ds-base: 389-ds-base: Heap buffer overflow in sasl_io_recv() via padded SASL UNBIND (CVE-2026-11610)\n\n* 389-ds-base: 389-ds-base: integer overflow in SASL packet length bypasses size limit leading to heap buffer overflow (CVE-2026-11774)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
